  Nkosentsha Shezi, of pro-black business group RET Champion, says that they will be picketing at Luthuli House to ensure that the ANC gets rid of Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan. Video: Samkelo Mtshali
 


“If Gordhan is not stopped in his trail, the ANC may lose credibility in the face of both black business and the working class community. Pravin Gordhan has become a law unto himself.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

“He founded an illegal and rogue unit at Sars and he has continued to employ his children, friends and associates in government entities at the expense of the people who voted the ANC to power,” says Shezi. 
He says that Gordhan was directing Transnet board chairman Popo Molefe and his board to suspend Siyabonga Gama as CEO “despite impressive results and unproven allegations”.
"He (Gordhan) wants to replace him (Gama) with lackeys who will capture Transnet on his behalf,” says Shezi.
